#Re-Identification of Zebrafish using Metric Learning

Zebrafish are commonly used by biologists to test and analyze different drugs, group behaviors and much more. The movement pattern of zebrafish is, however, highly erratic and therefore hard to track. Re-identification is therefore an essential step in the tracking pipeline, in order to connect the generated tracklets. Tracking of zebrafish has traditionally been conducted with a top-view focused approach, discarding the visually rich side-view perspective. https://www.kaggle.com/aalborguniversity/aau-zebrafish-reid#Vid1_0001.png
